      <bioghist id="aspace_72c733690bfbd589589b1008cd2862ac">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Rudy Vallée (1901-1986, born Hubert Prior Vallée) was a popular saxophonist, singer and bandleader in the first half of the 20th century. First of the genre of singers known as "crooners", Vallée attended Yale University, graduating in 1929. He named himself "Rudy" after the influential saxophonist Rudy Wiedoeft, and after graduation he formed the band, "Rudy Vallée and the Connecticut Yankees".</p>
         <p>Vallée went on to become a mass media pop star. He hosted several popular radio shows, and acted in films and Broadway musicals.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_43b6451ef7045badcfbf9b940717efbf">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The Collection contains photographs, clippings, programs, radio and TV scripts, memorabilia, and some audiovisual material.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_f72c9a01050f7b24af382d5f74dbbeef">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The collection is organized into four series: I. Photographs, II. Memorabilia, III. Scripts, and IV. Audiovisual material.</p>  
      </arrangement>
